Cape Town’s Disaster Risk Management Centre has been placed on high alert ahead of an expected storm on Tuesday. Strong winds, rough seas and heavy rain have been forecast for most of Tuesday and Wednesday. Disaster Management spokesperson, Charlotte Powell says, “Strong to gale force winds expected throughout the day along the coast. South west swells also increasing to five metres along that same stretch of coast line.” She adds “Vessels will have difficulty in navigating, risk of capsizing. Some disruption for small harbours may occur.” “Beachfront activities such as swimming and angling are not advised.” Related video click below: 